{"questionId":"7638","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{32}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>32</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is formed when a nucleus of deuterium (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{1}^{2}{\\text{H}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>H</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>) collides with a nucleus of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{31}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>31</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>. The radius of a deuterium nucleus is 1.5 fm.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State what is meant by decay constant.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>probability of decay of a nucleus ✔</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>the fraction of the number of nuclei that decay</p>\n<p>in one/the next second</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>per unit time ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"7638","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.6d.i","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"State what is meant by decay constant.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics","12.2 – Nuclear physics","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}